line_1: "And this proud man, so young and so untried!"
line_2: "So long successful in my art," she cried,

line_1: A dupe to follies yet untry'd,
line_2: And sick of pleasures, scarce enjoy'd!
Sets a Maid, to rise a Bride.

line_1: Some Reflections on Death, and its Terrors untry'd,
line_2: Some Scorn for the Shepherd, some Flashings of Pride

line_1: Dread separation! on the depth untry'd
line_2: How dreary is the gulph, how dark, how void,

line_1: Nor one well-weigh'd Expedient leave untry'd,
line_2: Grow still more earnest as they are deny'd,

line_1: And felt a growing passion yet untry'd:
line_2: The wounded Hebrew for the virgin sigh'd,

line_1: In all the Methods of Deceit untry'd.
line_2: Averse to Vanity, Revenge, and Pride,

line_1: Disdainful soaring up to heights untry'd.
Till fresh and lightsome, every power untried,
line_2: The starting fugitive leaps by his side,

line_1: Thro' wond'rous scenes of being yet untry'd,
line_2: From strength to strength our souls for ever guide,

line_1: Hear my request, for something yet untry'd,
line_2: And swear by Styx, I shall not be deny'd.
